01/11/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The families of those who went missing during the Balkan conflicts of the 1990s are demanding that the search for remains be speeded up.
About 100 representatives of associations of families of missing people from the region attended a meeting in Opatija, Croatia, on Sunday (31 October) and called for bringing those responsible for the wars to justice.
(AFP, HINA, HRT - 31/10/04;
HINA - 30/10/04)
